name: The Herlockers
bio:
Tribe of 6  that lived in a self-renovated vintage trailer for 4 years, now converting a van.
TRAVEL • ADVENTURE  • ROADSCHOOL

social_posts.post_text:
I’m not sure what the significance of finding 150+ sand dollars at the start of the New Year could be - but the word that comes to mind is Abundance. We have learned so much in our first year as business owners and building a community in a new place. There are no failures, only lessons, amiright?! So heading into 2023 with lots of lessons learned and the hope that this year will be abundant in joy, health, loyal friendships, successful business endeavors, ect ect. 
•
*Disclaimer - All creatures were kept alive, none were harmed or removed from the beach*
Birthday weekend with friends in the mountains - my cup is so full!!
Our first cenote in Mexico. A little history lesson on Mayan culture, a refreshing swim in clear water, and a fish pedicure - that’s what we call a solid day traveling with kids!
My beach babies 🥰
Romi really knows how to vacation - I’m pretty sure her arms were imprinted into this tube ☺️.
Twinning! Love my boys 🥰 @this.old.trailer
Highlights from our time in Mexico - it was truly a wonderful vacation and we came back to Asheville a few shades tanner and a few pounds heavier from the delicious food.

It’s hard to believe that the toddler that pretended to be a dog for a solid year of his life would turn into this caring, joyful, big kid. He traded the puppy costume in for a hat collection - and it’s rare to see him without one. Jasper is a sweet big brother and a goofy little brother, and makes sure to remind his sisters of all poop-talk that they might have missed out on without a brother in the mix. It’s been so fun watching him grow into this thoughtful and creative young man. His goal for year seven is to play all the hockey and get really, really good! We love you, Allan Jasper, Happy Birthday!
I hope everyone enjoyed the weekend as much as Jasper enjoyed this chocolate donut.

TEN YEARS together and we celebrated with a solo camping trip with Bluey in the Blue Ridge Mountains. 
Our lives became interwoven when we were youngsters full of big dreams, and despite being 10 years wiser we still dream big- maybe even bigger. These years have been scattered with deep dark moments and exceedingly bright ones, to get lost in either of them would be a mistake - drowning in the bad or chasing after the high of good times. I would much rather recollect by zooming out and viewing the pixelation of our years together, recognizing that the dark moments are specks in a sea of greys and whites, mixed in with bold highlighted memories. Focusing on the big, beautiful picture that we have created together - the gradient of two lives connected. I love you @this.old.trailer - happy anniversary!

*NINE*
Happy Birthday sweet Margo!!! 
You are an avid reader, rejoicing when we have time to visit the library and leaving with a stack full of books. You are deeply considerate of all those around you, always thinking of others and giving when you can. Thankfully, you have not lost your sense of style, and feel firmly about the clothes that display your beautiful personality. You are strong, crushing it at every sport you try, and this year one of your goals is to conquer a V4 at the rock climbing gym (which you definitely will - probably even next week). 
In Waldorf the nine-year-change marks the age that you move inward to outward and navigate the exodus from early childhood into a more conscious state - identifying your place in the world and not just inside your family. Although this sounds like an awkward, confusing process - I have watched you take on the hardest of challenges head first with such grace and I’m confident that this year will be no different.
I hope you keep writing songs, keep drawing cats, keep wearing pigtails everyday, and keep rolling on those new Heelys. Most importantly, keep shining that glowing light. 
I love you, Margo!!!

A visit to the Georgia Aquarium before Georgi’s divisional competition. The perfect way to continue birthday celebrations for Margo. Some highlights for the kids were the playful dolphins, the penguin that loved Romi’s stuffed animal, and having the opportunity to feed the otters (not on video because we were living in the moment 😜).

Incredibly proud of Georgi for placing 7th in Divisionals today!! The top 6 made it nationals so unfortunately she missed the cutoff, but she congratulated all her competitors and walked away feeling stoked for next season. Now to train hard for bouldering nationals next month - no rest for this committed athlete!
The warehouse is in full bloom, there are so many cool projects happening over @rom.customs !
The difference 11 years can make. @kaceyhalehuffman
I think we have died and gone to bunny heaven. I wouldn’t be surprised if Jasper tried to smuggle one in his backpack for the plane ride home.
Big Happy Birthday to this stud !!! Love you @this.old.trailer ❤️.

Words cannot begin to describe the fun we had in Idaho, so I’ll let this video show the incredible, action-packed trip with @kaceyhalehuffman and fam - it was an unforgettable experience for all of us!

Romi opted for land tubing after her first float down the rapid-river in Lava Hot Springs. The older kids went down 4+ times and convinced me to go down the waterfall section (clearly marked with danger warning signs😳). Can’t argue with this kid, playing it safe in style.

We recently moved into a new house, and the house is wonderful but the front yard blueberries are the main attraction. We have been filling our bowls with these blue beauties every morning, evening, and still have some to spare for the birds to have their fill.
End of summer camping trip with the family, unintentionally matching tent and van 💙

Grayson Highlands through the ages.
•
This magical wild pony land holds so many wonderful family memories, each visit special in its own way.
Creating a dream room for these girls, one paint sample at a time. Taking a break from painters tape for a few months but I think the rainbow was worth it 🌈.

FOURTEEN
I cant believe it even as I type it out! When I was pregnant with Georgi and I found out she was a girl my mind immediately flashed ahead to these moments, this mother- teenage daughter relationship; most likely due to an over-indulgence of Gilmore Girls. That was a lifetime ago, and yet it was yesterday. Not only did she make me a mother, she made me who I am today and I could not be more proud of her! These days are better than i could have ever imagined and here are some photos that describe 14-year-old Georgi. She finally got the hedgehog she has been begging for since she was a toddler (turns out that wasn’t a phase that would pass). Rock climbing is her top priority and her determination and strength are such an inspiration. She is the greatest big sister, and Romi’s favorite playmate! Not making an appearance but worth noting are  her Air Jordans that she splurged on with babysitting money, keeping meticulously clean and crease free. She is beautiful, inside and out and I cannot believe I get to be her mom! I hope this year is filled with my favorite car conversations driving from school to the rock climbing gym, competitive game playing (namely ping-pong and Rummikub) , bubble tea sipping, hi-chew gas station runs, bringing her new pet “Mr. Peekaboo Snuggles” on outings around town, and laughing until there are tears in our eyes. I love you so much … words cannot begin to express how much you mean to all of us @georgi.climbs. Happy Birthday!!!
2023 Mountain State Fair in a nutshell. Sugar and spinning detox for the rest of the year.
Chopped my hair and did a fun photo shoot with Romi Girl - hard to believe her birthday month is here and these are the last few weeks as a 3 year old!
Pumpkin carving with my pumpkins 🎃

Time to get Bluey into the shop to get repainted and spruced up. Don’t worry, I think we will stick with Blue 💙. Follow @rom.customs to see what we have in store for expanding the interior living space as well!

Every birthday comes with a twinge of grief. It’s hard to say goodbye to this 3-year-old version of our child but we are overjoyed to welcome the Big 4s! Romi is an absolute joy - full of confidence and spreading glitter from her golden heart wherever she goes. Always the baby of the family, we love you and love celebrating you! Happy 4th Birthday Romi!!!

Saying goodbye is heart wrenching. Words fail to express how much this dog means to our family, so here is a mix of pictures from the past eleven years of loyal protection and unconditional love. Rest easy sweet Luna, you are so missed ❤️.
A Charleston Thanksgiving - (sounds like the next hallmark movie title). Time well-spent with family and a few wiggly trout.

The best way to spread holiday cheer is to sing loud for all the hear!
#hippopotamus #hippohero
Decorated the tree without a single ornament breaking, a Christmas miracle!!
A holiday spent with family in this place we love so much - it doesn’t get much better. 🎅 🌊
Welcome to the fam, pup! We are all smitten with the newest member. Although she will never replace our Luna, we are overjoyed to have a Shepherd keeping us company once again.
First of many walks with this pup in tow and feeling grateful for this little, beautiful life together ❤️.
